9552671595

Selenium WebDriver Browser Commands
=====================================
1.get(url): open application
2.getTitle(): get the current application title
3.getCurrentUrl(): get the current url of application
4.getPageSource(): get the source code
Multiple window handling
-------------------------
5.getWindowHandle()
6.getWindowHandles()

7.close(): close current active window/session
8.quit(): close all open windows by selenium

Selenium Navigation commands
=================================
Selenium support Navigation Interface

1.to(url):Navigate to application
-------------------------------
driver.navigate().to(url)

2.back()
-----------------
driver.navigate().back()

3.forward()
---------------
driver.navigate().forward()

4.refresh()
---------------------
driver.navigate().refresh()


===============================================
What is WebElement in Selenium
===============================
Any GUI element from application is called WebElement
Technically WebElement is interface in Selenium

How to automate any WebElement
================================
1.Get the address of WebElement form the WebPage(Identification)
2.Perform action on WebElement

How to identify WebElement
==============================
Selenium Support Locators to identify WebElement

What is Locator?
===================
Locator is address of WebElement from WebPage

Selenium Support total 8 locators
===============================
1.By id (primary)
2.By name
3.By className
4.By linkText
5.By partialLinkText
6.By tagName

Dynamic Locator
==================
7.By cssSelector
8 By xpath

Selenium 4 support Relative locators
-----------------------------------------
For Identifications selenium support two methods
------------------------------------------------
1.findElement()

2.findElements()

==================================
WebElement Validation Methods
=============================
1.isDisplayed()
2.isEnabled()
3.isSelected()





















































